<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=220&amp;p=1438#p1438"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Smooth sprites falling from Screen Top]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=220&amp;p=1438#p1438"><![CDATA[
You could enable background and sprite drawing only from scanline 8 on... Leave both disabled and have a mapper generate an IRQ at scanline 8, and in the IRQ routine you enable both. You could also use some timed code...<br /><br />This way you can make sure your sprite will not "magically" appear, but you'll get an 8 pixel border at the top of the screen, muck like the one you get when you enable clipping of the 8 leftmost pixels of the screen.<br /><br />If you clip the top and the left you could have your sprites enter the screen smoothly. Although, like Memblers said, it really isn't visible on an actual TV, you might just want to be safe.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Sat Mar 05, 2005 7:29 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
